title: Sea Currents To Connectivity Transformation — seagraph
Sea Currents To Connectivity Transformation — seagraph
text: component_u SpatRaster object horizontal direction. component_v SpatRaster object vertical direction. mask_shapefile Optional sf SpatVector object masking component_u component_v SpatRaster objects. default value NULL, indicating mask performed. k_neighbors Number \(k\) nearest neighbors use. Default 7.

title: Sea Currents To Connectivity Transformation — seagraph
text: Sea currents data input transformed weighted directed graph connectivity data. Every grid cell nad corner component_u component_v considered separate graph node. connectivity data provided sfnetwork, sf, edge list adjacency matrix form. additional data.frame correspondence indices coordinates edge list adjacency matrix returned well. weights outputs minmax-scaled \([0-1]\). Extent, resolution coordinate system must component_u component_v; otherwise error stops function's execution. case mask_shapefile provided, internally assured resolution coordinates component_u warining prompted.

title: Sea Currents To Connectivity Transformation — seagraph
text: SeaGraph object, list containing following elements: sfnetwork: sfnetwork object representing graph coordinates connectivity map. sf: sf data.frame object representing 'LINESTRING' rows connections nodes. edge_list: matrix object representing edge list,  source (''), destination ('') weight ('weight') connection returned. adj_mat: matrix object representing weighted adjacency matrix nodes. ID_coords: data.frame object correspondence indices coordinates edge list (edge_list) adjacency matrix (adj_mat).
